info.title: Amazon EC2 NAT Gateways (Amazon VPC) API
info.description: The API for management NAT Gateways (Amazon VPC)

get.summary: Creates a NAT gateway in the specified subnet.
get.description: Creates a NAT gateway in the specified subnet.

parameters.name: AllocationId
parameters.description: The allocation ID of an Elastic IP address to associate with the NAT gateway. If the Elastic      IP address is associated with another resource, you must first disassociate it.

parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description: Unique, case-sensitive identifier you provide to ensure the idempotency of the request. For more information, see How to Ensure Idempotency.

parameters.name: SubnetId
parameters.description: The subnet in which to create the NAT gateway.

parameters.name: NatGatewayId
parameters.description: The ID of the NAT gateway.

get.summary: Describes one or more of the your NAT gateways.
get.description: Describes one or more of the your NAT gateways.

parameters.name: MaxResults
parameters.description: The maximum number of items to return for this request. The request returns a token that you can specify in a subsequent call to get the next set of results.

parameters.name: NatGatewayId.N
parameters.description: One or more NAT gateway IDs.

parameters.name: NextToken
parameters.description: The token to retrieve the next page of results.
